<item>
            <title>[LU-19763] Enable TCP zerocopy sending by default</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19763</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It turned out that the change introduced by&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12945&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12945&lt;/a&gt; impacts network performance significantly because it disables zerocopy in the sending path in the VM. During my LNet throughput test, it reduced the throughput by more than 30%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d propose to add a module parameter to optionally disable it because it will hit the issue only for debug kernels. In fact, we should disable it by default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre has been used widely in cloud, we should fix this ASAP. I will work on patch soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
